{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm delighted to be here."},{"time":2000,"text":"I'm honored by the invitation, and thanks."},{"time":5000,"text":"I would love to talk about stuff that I'm interested in,"},{"time":8000,"text":"but unfortunately, I suspect that what I'm interested in"},{"time":10000,"text":"won't interest many other people."},{"time":13000,"text":"First off, my badge says I'm an astronomer."},{"time":15000,"text":"I would love to talk about my astronomy,"},{"time":17000,"text":"but I suspect that the number of people who are interested in radiative transfer"},{"time":20000,"text":"in non-gray atmospheres"},{"time":22000,"text":"and polarization of light in Jupiter's upper atmosphere"},{"time":24000,"text":"are the number of people who'd fit in a bus shelter."},{"time":26000,"text":"So I'm not going to talk about that."},{"time":28000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":30000,"text":"It would be just as much fun"},{"time":32000,"text":"to talk about some stuff that happened in 1986 and 1987,"},{"time":35000,"text":"when a computer hacker is breaking into our systems"},{"time":38000,"text":"over at Lawrence Berkeley Labs."},{"time":40000,"text":"And I caught the guys,"},{"time":42000,"text":"and they turned out to be working for what was then the Soviet KGB,"},{"time":46000,"text":"and stealing information and selling it."},{"time":48000,"text":"And I'd love to talk about that -- and it'd be fun --"},{"time":52000,"text":"but, 20 years later ..."},{"time":55000,"text":"I find computer security, frankly, to be kind of boring."},{"time":57000,"text":"It's tedious."},{"time":59000,"text":"I'm --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":60000,"text":"The first time you do something, it's science."},{"time":64000,"text":"The second time, it's engineering."},{"time":67000,"text":"A third time, it's just being a technician."},{"time":70000,"text":"I'm a scientist. Once I do something, I do something else."},{"time":73000,"text":"So, I'm not going to talk about that."},{"time":75000,"text":"Nor am I going to talk about what I think are obvious statements from my first book,"},{"time":82000,"text":"\"Silicon Snake Oil,\" or my second book,"},{"time":86000,"text":"nor am I going to talk about"},{"time":88000,"text":"why I believe computers don't belong in schools."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91000,"text":"I feel that there's a massive and bizarre idea going around"},{"time":95000,"text":"that we have to bring more computers into schools."},{"time":99000,"text":"My idea is: no! No!"},{"time":101000,"text":"Get them out of schools, and keep them out of schools."},{"time":105000,"text":"And I'd love to talk about this,"},{"time":107000,"text":"but I think the argument is so obvious to anyone who's hung around a fourth grade classroom"},{"time":112000,"text":"that it doesn't need much talking about --"},{"time":116000,"text":"but I guess I may be very wrong about that,"},{"time":118000,"text":"and everything else that I've said."},{"time":119000,"text":"So don't go back and read my dissertation."},{"time":121000,"text":"It probably has lies in it as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123000,"text":"Having said that, I outlined my talk about five minutes ago."},{"time":127000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":130000,"text":"And if you look at it over here,"},{"time":132000,"text":"the main thing I wrote on my thumb was the future."},{"time":135000,"text":"I'm supposed to talk about the future, yes?"},{"time":138000,"text":"Oh, right. And my feeling is, asking me to talk about the future is bizarre,"},{"time":145000,"text":"because I've got gray hair,"},{"time":147000,"text":"and so, it's kind of silly for me to talk about the future."},{"time":153000,"text":"In fact, I think that if you really want to know what the future's going to be,"},{"time":157000,"text":"if you really want to know about the future,"},{"time":159000,"text":"don't ask a technologist, a scientist, a physicist."},{"time":163000,"text":"No! Don't ask somebody who's writing code."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170000,"text":"No, if you want to know what society's going to be like in 20 years,"},{"time":175000,"text":"ask a kindergarten teacher."},{"time":177000,"text":"They know."},{"time":180000,"text":"In fact, don't ask just any kindergarten teacher,"},{"time":183000,"text":"ask an experienced one."},{"time":185000,"text":"They're the ones who know what society is going to be like in another generation."},{"time":189000,"text":"I don't. Nor, I suspect,"},{"time":191000,"text":"do many other people who are talking about what the future will bring."},{"time":194000,"text":"Certainly, all of us can imagine these cool new things"},{"time":198000,"text":"that are going to be there."},{"time":199000,"text":"But to me, things aren't the future."},{"time":203000,"text":"What I ask myself is, what's society is going to be like,"},{"time":206000,"text":"when the kids today are phenomenally good at text messaging"},{"time":212000,"text":"and spend a huge amount of on-screen time,"},{"time":215000,"text":"but have never gone bowling together?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":221000,"text":"Change is happening, and the change that is happening"},{"time":224000,"text":"is not one that is in software."},{"time":227000,"text":"But that's not what I'm going to talk about."},{"time":228000,"text":"I'd love to talk about it, it'd be fun,"},{"time":231000,"text":"but I want to talk about what I'm doing now. What am I doing now?"},{"time":234000,"text":"Oh -- the other thing that I think I'd like to talk about"},{"time":236000,"text":"is right over here. Right over here."},{"time":240000,"text":"Is that visible? What I'd like to talk about is one-sided things."},{"time":246000,"text":"I would dearly love to talk about"},{"time":248000,"text":"things that have one side."},{"time":251000,"text":"Because I love Mobius loops. I not only love Mobius loops,"},{"time":255000,"text":"but I'm one of the very few people,"},{"time":258000,"text":"if not the only person in the world, that makes Klein bottles."},{"time":261000,"text":"Right away, I hope that all of your eyes glaze over."},{"time":264000,"text":"This is a Klein bottle."},{"time":267000,"text":"For those of you in the audience who know,"},{"time":270000,"text":"you roll your eyes and say, yup, I know all about it."},{"time":272000,"text":"It's one sided. It's a bottle whose inside is its outside."},{"time":274000,"text":"It has zero volume. And it's non-orientable."},{"time":277000,"text":"It has wonderful properties."},{"time":279000,"text":"If you take two Mobius loops and sew their common edge together,"},{"time":281000,"text":"you get one of these, and I make them out of glass."},{"time":284000,"text":"And I'd love to talk to you about this,"},{"time":286000,"text":"but I don't have much in the way of ... things to say because --"},{"time":292000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":294000,"text":"(Chris Anderson: I've got a cold.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":295000,"text":"However, the \"D\" in TED of course stands for design."},{"time":302000,"text":"Just two weeks ago I made --"},{"time":304000,"text":"you know, I've been making small, medium and big Klein bottles for the trade."},{"time":310000,"text":"But what I've just made --"},{"time":314000,"text":"and I'm delighted to show you, first time in public here."},{"time":323000,"text":"This is a Klein bottle wine bottle,"},{"time":328000,"text":"which, although in four dimensions"},{"time":331000,"text":"it shouldn't be able to hold any fluid at all,"},{"time":334000,"text":"it's perfectly capable of doing so"},{"time":336000,"text":"because our universe has only three spatial dimensions."},{"time":338000,"text":"And because our universe is only three spatial dimensions,"},{"time":341000,"text":"it can hold fluids."},{"time":344000,"text":"So it's highly -- that one's the cool one."},{"time":349000,"text":"That was a month of my life."},{"time":354000,"text":"But although I would love to talk about topology with you, I'm not going to."},{"time":359000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":365000,"text":"Instead, I'm going to mention my mom,"},{"time":370000,"text":"who passed away last summer."},{"time":373000,"text":"Had collected photographs of me, as mothers will do."},{"time":376000,"text":"Could somebody put this guy up?"},{"time":378000,"text":"And I looked over her album"},{"time":382000,"text":"and she had collected a picture of me, standing --"},{"time":385000,"text":"well, sitting -- in 1969, in front of a bunch of dials."},{"time":390000,"text":"And I looked at it, and said, oh my god,"},{"time":393000,"text":"that was me, when I was working at the electronic music studio!"},{"time":395000,"text":"As a technician, repairing and maintaining"},{"time":399000,"text":"the electronic music studio at SUNY Buffalo. And wow!"},{"time":403000,"text":"Way back machine. And I said to myself, oh yeah!"},{"time":409000,"text":"And it sent me back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413000,"text":"Soon after that, I found in another picture that she had, a picture of me."},{"time":421000,"text":"This guy over here of course is me."},{"time":425000,"text":"This man is Robert Moog,"},{"time":427000,"text":"the inventor of the Moog synthesizer,"},{"time":429000,"text":"who passed away this past August."},{"time":434000,"text":"Robert Moog was a generous, kind person, extraordinarily competent engineer."},{"time":439000,"text":"A musician who took time from his life to teach me,"},{"time":445000,"text":"a sophomore, a freshman at SUNY Buffalo."},{"time":448000,"text":"He'd come up from Trumansburg to teach me"},{"time":453000,"text":"not just about the Moog synthesizer, but we'd be sitting there --"},{"time":457000,"text":"I'm studying physics at the time. This is 1969, 70, 71."},{"time":460000,"text":"We're studying physics, I'm studying physics,"},{"time":462000,"text":"and he's saying, \"That's a good thing to do."},{"time":464000,"text":"Don't get caught up in electronic music if you're doing physics.\""},{"time":466000,"text":"Mentoring me. He'd come up and"},{"time":469000,"text":"spend hours and hours with me."},{"time":473000,"text":"He wrote a letter of recommendation for me to get into graduate school."},{"time":476000,"text":"In the background, my bicycle."},{"time":478000,"text":"I realize that this picture was taken at a friend's living room."},{"time":481000,"text":"Bob Moog came by and hauled a whole pile of equipment"},{"time":484000,"text":"to show Greg Flint and I things about this."},{"time":486000,"text":"We sat around talking about Fourier transforms,"},{"time":488000,"text":"Bessel functions, modulation transfer functions,"},{"time":491000,"text":"stuff like this."},{"time":496000,"text":"Bob's passing this past summer has been a loss to all of us."},{"time":499000,"text":"Anyone who's a musician has been profoundly influenced by Robert Moog."},{"time":504000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":506000,"text":"And I'll just say what I'm about to do. What I'm about to do --"},{"time":511000,"text":"I hope you can recognize that there's a distorted sine wave,"},{"time":515000,"text":"almost a triangular wave upon this Hewlett-Packard oscilloscope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521000,"text":"Oh, cool. I can get to this place over here, right?"},{"time":526000,"text":"Kids. Kids is what I'm going to talk about -- is that okay?"},{"time":528000,"text":"It says kids over here, that's what I'd like to talk about."},{"time":532000,"text":"I've decided that, for me at least,"},{"time":536000,"text":"I don't have a big enough head."},{"time":541000,"text":"So I think locally and I act locally."},{"time":544000,"text":"I feel that the best way I can help out anything is to help out very, very locally."},{"time":548000,"text":"So Ph.D. this, and degree there, and the yadda yadda."},{"time":553000,"text":"I was talking about this stuff to"},{"time":557000,"text":"some schoolteachers about a year ago."},{"time":559000,"text":"And one of them, several of them would come up to me and say,"},{"time":561000,"text":"\"Well, how come you ain't teaching?\""},{"time":563000,"text":"And I said, \"Well, I've taught graduate --"},{"time":564000,"text":"I've had graduate students, I've taught undergraduate classes.\""},{"time":567000,"text":"No, they said, \"If you're so into kids and all this stuff,"},{"time":569000,"text":"how come you ain't over here on the front lines?"},{"time":572000,"text":"Put your money where you mouth is.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":576000,"text":"Is true. Is true. I teach eighth-grade science four days a week."},{"time":582000,"text":"Not just showing up every now and then."},{"time":584000,"text":"No, no, no, no, no. I take attendance."},{"time":588000,"text":"I take lunch hour. (Applause)"},{"time":591000,"text":"This is not -- no, no, no, this is not claps."},{"time":594000,"text":"I strongly suggest that this is a good thing for each of you to do."},{"time":598000,"text":"Not just show up to class every now and then."},{"time":600000,"text":"Teach a solid week. Okay, I'm teaching three-quarters time, but good enough."},{"time":604000,"text":"One of the things that I've done for my science students"},{"time":606000,"text":"is to tell them, \"Look, I'm going to teach you college-level physics."},{"time":609000,"text":"No calculus, I'll cut out that."},{"time":611000,"text":"You won't need to know trig."},{"time":613000,"text":"But you will need to know eighth-grade algebra,"},{"time":616000,"text":"and we're going to do serious experiments."},{"time":618000,"text":"None of this open-to-chapter-seven-and-do-all-the-odd-problem-sets."},{"time":621000,"text":"We're going to be doing genuine physics.\""},{"time":624000,"text":"And that's one of the things I thought I'd do right now."},{"time":626000,"text":"(High-pitched tone)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":629000,"text":"Oh, before I even turn that on,"},{"time":631000,"text":"one of the things that we did about three weeks ago in my class --"},{"time":635000,"text":"this is through the lens, and one of the things we used a lens for"},{"time":637000,"text":"was to measure the speed of light."},{"time":639000,"text":"My students in El Cerrito -- with my help, of course,"},{"time":642000,"text":"and with the help of a very beat up oscilloscope --"},{"time":645000,"text":"measured the speed of light."},{"time":646000,"text":"We were off by 25 percent. How many eighth graders do you know of"},{"time":651000,"text":"who have measured the speed of light?"},{"time":653000,"text":"In addition to that, we've measured the speed of sound."},{"time":656000,"text":"I'd love to measure the speed of light here."},{"time":658000,"text":"I was all set to do it and I was thinking, \"Aw man,\""},{"time":660000,"text":"I was just going to impose upon the powers that be,"},{"time":663000,"text":"and measure the speed of light."},{"time":664000,"text":"And I'm all set to do it. I'm all set to do it,"},{"time":668000,"text":"but then it turns out that to set up here, you have like 10 minutes to set up!"},{"time":672000,"text":"And there's no time to do it."},{"time":674000,"text":"So, next time, maybe, I'll measure the speed of light!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":676000,"text":"But meanwhile, let's measure the speed of sound!"},{"time":678000,"text":"Well, the obvious way to measure the speed of sound"},{"time":680000,"text":"is to bounce sound off something and look at the echo."},{"time":683000,"text":"But, probably -- one of my students, Ariel [unclear], said,"},{"time":688000,"text":"\"Could we measure the speed of light using the wave equation?\""},{"time":691000,"text":"And all of you know the wave equation is"},{"time":693000,"text":"the frequency times the wavelength of any wave ..."},{"time":699000,"text":"is a constant. When the frequency goes up,"},{"time":702000,"text":"the wavelength comes down. Wavelength goes up,"},{"time":705000,"text":"frequency goes down. So, if we have a wave here --"},{"time":710000,"text":"over here, that's what's interesting --"},{"time":714000,"text":"as the pitch goes up, things get closer,"},{"time":717000,"text":"pitch goes down, things stretch out."},{"time":721000,"text":"Right? This is simple physics."},{"time":723000,"text":"All of you know this from eighth grade, remember?"},{"time":726000,"text":"What they didn't tell you in physics -- in eighth-grade physics --"},{"time":730000,"text":"but they should have, and I wish they had,"},{"time":733000,"text":"was that if you multiply the frequency times the wavelength of sound"},{"time":737000,"text":"or light, you get a constant."},{"time":741000,"text":"And that constant is the speed of sound."},{"time":744000,"text":"So, in order to measure the speed of sound,"},{"time":747000,"text":"all I've got to do is know its frequency. Well, that's easy."},{"time":751000,"text":"I've got a frequency counter right here."},{"time":753000,"text":"Set it up to around A, above A, above A. There's an A, more or less."},{"time":758000,"text":"Now, so I know the frequency."},{"time":763000,"text":"It's 1.76 kilohertz. I measure its wavelength."},{"time":768000,"text":"All I need now is to flip on another beam,"},{"time":771000,"text":"and the bottom beam is me talking, right?"},{"time":774000,"text":"So anytime I talk, you'd see it on the screen."},{"time":779000,"text":"I'll put it over here, and as I move this away from the source,"},{"time":783000,"text":"you'll notice the spiral."},{"time":788000,"text":"The slinky moves. We're going through different nodes of the wave,"},{"time":793000,"text":"coming out this way."},{"time":795000,"text":"Those of you who are physicists, I hear you rolling your eyes,"},{"time":797000,"text":"but bear with me. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":799000,"text":"To measure the wavelength,"},{"time":802000,"text":"all I need to do is measure the distance from here --"},{"time":808000,"text":"one full wave -- over to here."},{"time":810000,"text":"From here to here is the wavelength of sound."},{"time":813000,"text":"So, I'll put a measuring tape here, measuring tape here, move it back over to here."},{"time":821000,"text":"I've moved the microphone 20 centimeters."},{"time":825000,"text":"0.2 meters from here, back to here, 20 centimeters."},{"time":832000,"text":"OK, let's go back to Mr. Elmo."},{"time":838000,"text":"And we'll say the frequency is 1.76 kilohertz, or 1760."},{"time":845000,"text":"The wavelength was 0.2 meters."},{"time":849000,"text":"Let's figure out what this is."},{"time":853000,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":861000,"text":"1.76 times 0.2 over here is 352 meters per second."},{"time":868000,"text":"If you look it up in the book, it's really 343."},{"time":874000,"text":"But, here with kludgy material, and lousy drink --"},{"time":876000,"text":"we've been able to measure the speed of sound to --"},{"time":881000,"text":"not bad. Pretty good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":883000,"text":"All of which comes to what I wanted to say."},{"time":888000,"text":"Go back to this picture of me a million years ago."},{"time":893000,"text":"It was 1971, the Vietnam War was going on,"},{"time":898000,"text":"and I'm like, \"Oh my God!\""},{"time":901000,"text":"I'm studying physics: Landau, Lipschitz, Resnick and Halliday."},{"time":904000,"text":"I'm going home for a midterm. A riot's going on on campus."},{"time":906000,"text":"There's a riot! Hey, Elmo's done: off."},{"time":915000,"text":"There's a riot going on on campus,"},{"time":917000,"text":"and the police are chasing me, right?"},{"time":920000,"text":"I'm walking across campus. Cop comes and looks at me and says,"},{"time":923000,"text":"\"You! You're a student.\""},{"time":925000,"text":"Pulls out a gun. Goes boom!"},{"time":927000,"text":"And a tear gas canister the size of a Pepsi can goes by my head. Whoosh!"},{"time":931000,"text":"I get a breath of tear gas and I can't breathe."},{"time":934000,"text":"This cop comes after me with a rifle."},{"time":936000,"text":"He wants to clunk me over the head!"},{"time":938000,"text":"I'm saying, \"I got to clear out of here!\""},{"time":941000,"text":"I go running across campus quick as I can. I duck into Hayes Hall."},{"time":947000,"text":"It's one of these bell-tower buildings."},{"time":949000,"text":"The cop's chasing me."},{"time":951000,"text":"Chasing me up the first floor, second floor, third floor."},{"time":953000,"text":"Chases me into this room."},{"time":954000,"text":"The entranceway to the bell tower."},{"time":956000,"text":"I slam the door behind me, climb up,"},{"time":958000,"text":"go past this place where I see a pendulum ticking."},{"time":960000,"text":"And I'm thinking, \"Oh yeah,"},{"time":962000,"text":"the square root of the length is proportional to its period.\" (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":965000,"text":"I keep climbing up, go back."},{"time":967000,"text":"I go to a place where a dowel splits off."},{"time":969000,"text":"There's a clock, clock, clock, clock."},{"time":970000,"text":"The time's going backwards because I'm inside of it."},{"time":972000,"text":"I'm thinking of Lorenz contractions and Einsteinian relativity."},{"time":976000,"text":"I climb up, and there's this place, way in the back,"},{"time":979000,"text":"that you climb up this wooden ladder."},{"time":981000,"text":"I pop up the top, and there's a cupola."},{"time":983000,"text":"A dome, one of these ten-foot domes."},{"time":985000,"text":"I'm looking out and I'm seeing the cops bashing students' heads,"},{"time":988000,"text":"shooting tear gas, and watching students throwing bricks."},{"time":990000,"text":"And I'm asking, \"What am I doing here? Why am I here?\""},{"time":993000,"text":"Then I remember what my English teacher in high school said."},{"time":996000,"text":"Namely, that when they cast bells,"},{"time":1000000,"text":"they write inscriptions on them."},{"time":1003000,"text":"So, I wipe the pigeon manure off one of the bells, and I look at it."},{"time":1007000,"text":"I'm asking myself, \"Why am I here?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1010000,"text":"So, at this time, I'd like to tell you the words inscribed"},{"time":1014000,"text":"upon the Hayes Hall tower bells:"},{"time":1018000,"text":"\"All truth is one."},{"time":1023000,"text":"In this light, may science and religion endeavor here"},{"time":1029000,"text":"for the steady evolution of mankind, from darkness to light,"},{"time":1033000,"text":"from narrowness to broad-mindedness, from prejudice to tolerance."},{"time":1041000,"text":"It is the voice of life, which calls us to come and learn.\""},{"time":1049000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]}]}